\title{Plugin structure}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{version}{0.1.0}

\meta{description}{\startverb This skill should be used when the user asks to "create a plugin", "scaffold a plugin", "understand plugin structure", "organize plugin components", "set up plugin.json", "use ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}", "add commands/agents/skills/hooks", "configure auto-discovery", or needs guidance on plugin directory layout, manifest configuration, component organization, file naming conventions, or Claude Code plugin architecture best practices.\stopverb}

\subtree{
\title{Plugin Structure for Claude Code}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Claude Code plugins follow a standardized directory structure with automatic component discovery. Understanding this structure enables creating well-organized, maintainable plugins that integrate seamlessly with Claude Code.}

\p{\strong{Key concepts:}}

\ul{
\li{Conventional directory layout for automatic discovery}
\li{Manifest-driven configuration in \code{\startverb .claude-plugin/plugin.json\stopverb}}
\li{Component-based organization (commands, agents, skills, hooks)}
\li{\startverb Portable path references using `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}`\stopverb}
\li{Explicit vs. auto-discovered component loading}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Directory Structure}
\p{Every Claude Code plugin follows this organizational pattern:}

\pre{\startverb
plugin-name/
├── .claude-plugin/
│   └── plugin.json          # Required: Plugin manifest
├── commands/                 # Slash commands (.md files)
├── agents/                   # Subagent definitions (.md files)
├── skills/                   # Agent skills (subdirectories)
│   └── skill-name/
│       └── SKILL.md         # Required for each skill
├── hooks/
│   └── hooks.json           # Event handler configuration
├── .mcp.json                # MCP server definitions
└── scripts/                 # Helper scripts and utilities
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Critical rules:}}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Manifest location}: The \code{\startverb plugin.json\stopverb} manifest MUST be in \code{\startverb .claude-plugin/\stopverb} directory}
\li{\strong{Component locations}: All component directories (commands, agents, skills, hooks) MUST be at plugin root level, NOT nested inside \code{\startverb .claude-plugin/\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Optional components}: Only create directories for components the plugin actually uses}
\li{\strong{Naming convention}: Use kebab-case for all directory and file names}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Plugin Manifest (plugin.json)}
\p{The manifest defines plugin metadata and configuration. Located at \code{\startverb .claude-plugin/plugin.json\stopverb}:}

\subtree{
\title{Required Fields}
\pre{\startverb
{
  "name": "plugin-name"
}
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Name requirements:}}

\ul{
\li{Use kebab-case format (lowercase with hyphens)}
\li{Must be unique across installed plugins}
\li{No spaces or special characters}
\li{Example: \code{\startverb code-review-assistant\stopverb}, \code{\startverb test-runner\stopverb}, \code{\startverb api-docs\stopverb}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Recommended Metadata}
\pre{\startverb
{
  "name": "plugin-name",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Brief explanation of plugin purpose",
  "author": {
    "name": "Author Name",
    "email": "author@example.com",
    "url": "https://example.com"
  },
  "homepage": "https://docs.example.com",
  "repository": "https://github.com/user/plugin-name",
  "license": "MIT",
  "keywords": ["testing", "automation", "ci-cd"]
}
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Version format}: Follow semantic versioning (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH) \strong{Keywords}: Use for plugin discovery and categorization}
}

\subtree{
\title{Component Path Configuration}
\p{Specify custom paths for components (supplements default directories):}

\pre{\startverb
{
  "name": "plugin-name",
  "commands": "./custom-commands",
  "agents": ["./agents", "./specialized-agents"],
  "hooks": "./config/hooks.json",
  "mcpServers": "./.mcp.json"
}
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Important}: Custom paths supplement defaults—they don't replace them. Components in both default directories and custom paths will load.}

\p{\strong{Path rules:}}

\ul{
\li{Must be relative to plugin root}
\li{Must start with \code{\startverb ./\stopverb}}
\li{Cannot use absolute paths}
\li{Support arrays for multiple locations}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Component Organization}
\subtree{
\title{Commands}
\p{\strong{Location}: \code{\startverb commands/\stopverb} directory \strong{Format}: Markdown files with YAML frontmatter \strong{Auto-discovery}: All \code{\startverb .md\stopverb} files in \code{\startverb commands/\stopverb} load automatically}

\p{\strong{Example structure}:}

\pre{\startverb
commands/
├── review.md        # /review command
├── test.md          # /test command
└── deploy.md        # /deploy command
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{File format}:}

\pre{\startverb
---
name: command-name
description: Command description
---

Command implementation instructions...
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Usage}: Commands integrate as native slash commands in Claude Code}
}

\subtree{
\title{Agents}
\p{\strong{Location}: \code{\startverb agents/\stopverb} directory \strong{Format}: Markdown files with YAML frontmatter \strong{Auto-discovery}: All \code{\startverb .md\stopverb} files in \code{\startverb agents/\stopverb} load automatically}

\p{\strong{Example structure}:}

\pre{\startverb
agents/
├── code-reviewer.md
├── test-generator.md
└── refactorer.md
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{File format}:}

\pre{\startverb
---
description: Agent role and expertise
capabilities:
  - Specific task 1
  - Specific task 2
---

Detailed agent instructions and knowledge...
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Usage}: Users can invoke agents manually, or Claude Code selects them automatically based on task context}
}

\subtree{
\title{Skills}
\p{\strong{Location}: \code{\startverb skills/\stopverb} directory with subdirectories per skill \strong{Format}: Each skill in its own directory with \code{\startverb SKILL.md\stopverb} file \strong{Auto-discovery}: All \code{\startverb SKILL.md\stopverb} files in skill subdirectories load automatically}

\p{\strong{Example structure}:}

\pre{\startverb
skills/
├── api-testing/
│   ├── SKILL.md
│   ├── scripts/
│   │   └── test-runner.py
│   └── references/
│       └── api-spec.md
└── database-migrations/
    ├── SKILL.md
    └── examples/
        └── migration-template.sql
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{SKILL.md format}:}

\pre{\startverb
---
name: Skill Name
description: When to use this skill
version: 1.0.0
---

Skill instructions and guidance...
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Supporting files}: Skills can include scripts, references, examples, or assets in subdirectories}

\p{\strong{Usage}: Claude Code autonomously activates skills based on task context matching the description}
}

\subtree{
\title{Hooks}
\p{\strong{Location}: \code{\startverb hooks/hooks.json\stopverb} or inline in \code{\startverb plugin.json\stopverb} \strong{Format}: JSON configuration defining event handlers \strong{Registration}: Hooks register automatically when plugin enables}

\p{\strong{Example structure}:}

\pre{\startverb
hooks/
├── hooks.json           # Hook configuration
└── scripts/
    ├── validate.sh      # Hook script
    └── check-style.sh   # Hook script
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Configuration format}:}

\pre{\startverb
{
  "PreToolUse": [{
    "matcher": "Write|Edit",
    "hooks": [{
      "type": "command",
      "command": "bash ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks/scripts/validate.sh",
      "timeout": 30
    }]
  }]
}
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Available events}: PreToolUse, PostToolUse, Stop, SubagentStop, SessionStart, SessionEnd, UserPromptSubmit, PreCompact, Notification}

\p{\strong{Usage}: Hooks execute automatically in response to Claude Code events}
}

\subtree{
\title{MCP Servers}
\p{\strong{Location}: \code{\startverb .mcp.json\stopverb} at plugin root or inline in \code{\startverb plugin.json\stopverb} \strong{Format}: JSON configuration for MCP server definitions \strong{Auto-start}: Servers start automatically when plugin enables}

\p{\strong{Example format}:}

\pre{\startverb
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "server-name": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/servers/server.js"],
      "env": {
        "API_KEY": "${API_KEY}"
      }
    }
  }
}
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Usage}: MCP servers integrate seamlessly with Claude Code's tool system}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Portable Path References}
\subtree{
\title{${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}}
\pre{\startverb
Use `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}` environment variable for all intra-plugin path references:
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
{
  "command": "bash ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/run.sh"
}
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Why it matters}: Plugins install in different locations depending on:}

\ul{
\li{User installation method (marketplace, local, npm)}
\li{Operating system conventions}
\li{User preferences}
}

\p{\strong{Where to use it}:}

\ul{
\li{Hook command paths}
\li{MCP server command arguments}
\li{Script execution references}
\li{Resource file paths}
}

\p{\strong{Never use}:}

\ul{
\li{Hardcoded absolute paths (\code{\startverb /Users/name/plugins/...\stopverb})}
\li{Relative paths from working directory (\code{\startverb ./scripts/...\stopverb} in commands)}
\li{Home directory shortcuts (\code{\startverb ~/plugins/...\stopverb})}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Path Resolution Rules}
\p{\strong{In manifest JSON fields} (hooks, MCP servers):}

\pre{\startverb
"command": "${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/tool.sh"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{In component files} (commands, agents, skills):}

\pre{\startverb
Reference scripts at: ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/helper.py
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{In executed scripts}:}

\pre{\startverb
#!/bin/bash
# ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} available as environment variable
source "${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/lib/common.sh"
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{File Naming Conventions}
\subtree{
\title{Component Files}
\p{\strong{Commands}: Use kebab-case \code{\startverb .md\stopverb} files}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb code-review.md\stopverb} → \code{\startverb /code-review\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb run-tests.md\stopverb} → \code{\startverb /run-tests\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb api-docs.md\stopverb} → \code{\startverb /api-docs\stopverb}}
}

\p{\strong{Agents}: Use kebab-case \code{\startverb .md\stopverb} files describing role}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb test-generator.md\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb code-reviewer.md\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb performance-analyzer.md\stopverb}}
}

\p{\strong{Skills}: Use kebab-case directory names}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb api-testing/\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb database-migrations/\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb error-handling/\stopverb}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Supporting Files}
\p{\strong{Scripts}: Use descriptive kebab-case names with appropriate extensions}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb validate-input.sh\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb generate-report.py\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb process-data.js\stopverb}}
}

\p{\strong{Documentation}: Use kebab-case markdown files}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb api-reference.md\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb migration-guide.md\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb best-practices.md\stopverb}}
}

\p{\strong{Configuration}: Use standard names}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb hooks.json\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb .mcp.json\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb plugin.json\stopverb}}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Auto-Discovery Mechanism}
\p{Claude Code automatically discovers and loads components:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Plugin manifest}: Reads \code{\startverb .claude-plugin/plugin.json\stopverb} when plugin enables}
\li{\strong{Commands}: Scans \code{\startverb commands/\stopverb} directory for \code{\startverb .md\stopverb} files}
\li{\strong{Agents}: Scans \code{\startverb agents/\stopverb} directory for \code{\startverb .md\stopverb} files}
\li{\strong{Skills}: Scans \code{\startverb skills/\stopverb} for subdirectories containing \code{\startverb SKILL.md\stopverb}}
\li{\strong{Hooks}: Loads configuration from \code{\startverb hooks/hooks.json\stopverb} or manifest}
\li{\strong{MCP servers}: Loads configuration from \code{\startverb .mcp.json\stopverb} or manifest}
}

\p{\strong{Discovery timing}:}

\ul{
\li{Plugin installation: Components register with Claude Code}
\li{Plugin enable: Components become available for use}
\li{No restart required: Changes take effect on next Claude Code session}
}

\p{\strong{Override behavior}: Custom paths in \code{\startverb plugin.json\stopverb} supplement (not replace) default directories}
}

\subtree{
\title{Best Practices}
\subtree{
\title{Organization}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Logical grouping}: Group related components together}
\li{Put test-related commands, agents, and skills together}
\li{Create subdirectories in \code{\startverb scripts/\stopverb} for different purposes}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Minimal manifest}: Keep \code{\startverb plugin.json\stopverb} lean}
\li{Only specify custom paths when necessary}
\li{Rely on auto-discovery for standard layouts}
\li{Use inline configuration only for simple cases}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Documentation}: Include README files}
\li{Plugin root: Overall purpose and usage}
\li{Component directories: Specific guidance}
\li{Script directories: Usage and requirements}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Naming}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Consistency}: Use consistent naming across components}
\li{If command is \code{\startverb test-runner\stopverb}, name related agent \code{\startverb test-runner-agent\stopverb}}
\li{Match skill directory names to their purpose}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Clarity}: Use descriptive names that indicate purpose}
\li{Good: \code{\startverb api-integration-testing/\stopverb}, \code{\startverb code-quality-checker.md\stopverb}}
\li{Avoid: \code{\startverb utils/\stopverb}, \code{\startverb misc.md\stopverb}, \code{\startverb temp.sh\stopverb}}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Length}: Balance brevity with clarity}
\li{Commands: 2-3 words (\code{\startverb review-pr\stopverb}, \code{\startverb run-ci\stopverb})}
\li{Agents: Describe role clearly (\code{\startverb code-reviewer\stopverb}, \code{\startverb test-generator\stopverb})}
\li{Skills: Topic-focused (\code{\startverb error-handling\stopverb}, \code{\startverb api-design\stopverb})}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Portability}
\ol{
\li{\startverb **Always use ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}**: Never hardcode paths\stopverb}
\li{\strong{Test on multiple systems}: Verify on macOS, Linux, Windows}
\li{\strong{Document dependencies}: List required tools and versions}
\li{\strong{Avoid system-specific features}: Use portable bash/Python constructs}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Maintenance}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Version consistently}: Update version in plugin.json for releases}
\li{\strong{Deprecate gracefully}: Mark old components clearly before removal}
\li{\strong{Document breaking changes}: Note changes affecting existing users}
\li{\strong{Test thoroughly}: Verify all components work after changes}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Patterns}
\subtree{
\title{Minimal Plugin}
\p{Single command with no dependencies:}

\pre{\startverb
my-plugin/
├── .claude-plugin/
│   └── plugin.json    # Just name field
└── commands/
    └── hello.md       # Single command
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Full-Featured Plugin}
\p{Complete plugin with all component types:}

\pre{\startverb
my-plugin/
├── .claude-plugin/
│   └── plugin.json
├── commands/          # User-facing commands
├── agents/            # Specialized subagents
├── skills/            # Auto-activating skills
├── hooks/             # Event handlers
│   ├── hooks.json
│   └── scripts/
├── .mcp.json          # External integrations
└── scripts/           # Shared utilities
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Skill-Focused Plugin}
\p{Plugin providing only skills:}

\pre{\startverb
my-plugin/
├── .claude-plugin/
│   └── plugin.json
└── skills/
    ├── skill-one/
    │   └── SKILL.md
    └── skill-two/
        └── SKILL.md
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Troubleshooting}
\p{\strong{Component not loading}:}

\ul{
\li{Verify file is in correct directory with correct extension}
\li{Check YAML frontmatter syntax (commands, agents, skills)}
\li{Ensure skill has \code{\startverb SKILL.md\stopverb} (not \code{\startverb README.md\stopverb} or other name)}
\li{Confirm plugin is enabled in Claude Code settings}
}

\p{\strong{Path resolution errors}:}

\ul{
\li{\startverb Replace all hardcoded paths with `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}`\stopverb}
\li{Verify paths are relative and start with \code{\startverb ./\stopverb} in manifest}
\li{Check that referenced files exist at specified paths}
\li{\startverb Test with `echo $CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT` in hook scripts\stopverb}
}

\p{\strong{Auto-discovery not working}:}

\ul{
\li{Confirm directories are at plugin root (not in \code{\startverb .claude-plugin/\stopverb})}
\li{Check file naming follows conventions (kebab-case, correct extensions)}
\li{Verify custom paths in manifest are correct}
\li{Restart Claude Code to reload plugin configuration}
}

\p{\strong{Conflicts between plugins}:}

\ul{
\li{Use unique, descriptive component names}
\li{Namespace commands with plugin name if needed}
\li{Document potential conflicts in plugin README}
\li{Consider command prefixes for related functionality}
}

\p{For detailed examples and advanced patterns, see files in \code{\startverb references/\stopverb} and \code{\startverb examples/\stopverb} directories.}
}
}